                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "8 (a) It is given that \\(\\lambda\\) is an eigenvalue of the non-singular square matrix \\(\\mathbf{A}\\), with corresponding eigenvector \\(\\mathbf{e}\\).",
                        "bbox": [
                            78,
                            72,
                            916,
                            105
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Show that \\(\\mathbf{e}\\) is an eigenvector of \\(\\mathbf{A}^3\\) with corresponding eigenvalue \\(\\lambda^3\\). [2]",
                        "bbox": [
                            155,
                            117,
                            916,
                            138
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "label": "b",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "The matrix \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) is given by",
                        "bbox": [
                            118,
                            400,
                            320,
                            417
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "blockMath",
                        "blockMath": "\\[ \\mathbf{A} = \\begin{pmatrix} -1 & 3 & 4 \\\\ 0 & 1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & -2 & 5 \\end{pmatrix}. \\]",
                        "bbox": [
                            424,
                            425,
                            576,
                            481
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "(b) Show that the eigenvalues of \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) are \\(-1, 1\\) and \\(5\\). [2]",
                        "bbox": [
