                            928,
                            92
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "(d) Use the characteristic equation of \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) to show that \\((\\mathbf{A} - 2\\mathbf{I})^3 = a\\mathbf{A}^2 + b\\mathbf{A} + c\\mathbf{I}\\) where \\(a, b\\) and \\(c\\) are constants to be determined. [3]",
                        "bbox": [
